comments: Ayton (PHX) momentarily places two hands on Nurkic (POR) away from the ball and then removes the marginal contact shortly thereafter.
Lee (PHX) legally contests Hart's (POR) jump shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) takes less than 8 seconds to establish the ball in the frontcourt.
Nurkic (POR) places and immediately removes his hands from Ayton (PHX) as the offensive player is establishing screening position. The contact on the play is marginal.
Bridges (PHX) avoids stepping out of bounds while in possession of the ball.
Grant (POR) legally contests Lee's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Lee (PHX) places his hand on Hart's (POR) side and the contact is marginal as Hart goes to establish screening position.
Nurkic (POR) has his hands on Ayton's (PHX) side and his arms extend outwards as Ayton jumps towards the ball. The contact on the play is marginal.
Bridges (PHX) legally contests Grant's (POR) shot attempt in the post.
Booker (PHX) grasps and immediately releases Nurkic's (POR) jersey and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Lee (PHX) places a resting hand on Nurkic (POR) as he attempts to tip in the rebound and the contact during the play is marginal.

Paul (PHX) reaches up for the ball and some marginal contact occurs with Nurkic's (POR) head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Replay review of the out of bounds called on Lee (PHX) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Nurkic (POR) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and PHX is given possession.
Hart's (POR) arms extend out slightly as he releases away from Booker (PHX), who is attempting to establish himself in a screening position. The contact on the play is marginal.
Hart (POR) places his right forearm on Paul's (PHX) side and removes the marginal contact shortly thereafter during Paul's drive.
Winslow (POR) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Grant (POR) holds his hands on Ayton (PHX) and removes the marginal contact as the ball comes off of the rim.
Ayton (PHX) places a resting arm on Nurkic's (POR) back and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Nurkic (POR) lightly brushes Ayton's (PHX) hand during his tip-in attempt and the contact is marginal.
Hart (POR) establishes his right foot as his pivot and releases his dribble prior to sliding that foot forward.
Hart (POR) steps forward at the start of his drive and marginal contact occurs with Booker's (PHX) leg that Hart is able to play on through.
Ayton (PHX) legally contests Nurkic's (POR) jump shot attempt. After both players have returned to the floor and are backing away from the basket, incidental foot to foot contact occurs.
Nurkic (POR) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Johnson (POR) establishes himself in a screening position and marginal contact occurs as Craig (PHX) goes around the screen.
Nurkic's (POR) arm comes out slightly as he establishes screening position and marginal contact occurs with Bridges (PHX) as he goes over the pick.
Ayton (PHX) moves alongside Grant's (POR) path and marginal body contact occurs after the gather during the driving shot attempt.
Bridges (PHX) reaches up for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Nurkic's (POR) arm during the rebounding opportunity.
Bridges (PHX) brings a resting hand to Nurkic's (POR) side during the layup attempt and the contact at the basket is marginal.
Johnson (POR) has a foot on the lane line for more than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.

Bridges (PHX) brings two hands to the ball and gathers it on his right foot. He then comes down on two feet for his first step and can choose either foot as his pivot foot. He establishes his left foot as his pivot by stepping with his right and then leaves the ground and releases his shot attempt.
Nurkic's (POR) establishes himself in a screening position and his right arm comes out slightly and marginal contact occurs with Bridges (PHX).
Grant (POR) engages with Ayton (PHX) while the pass is in the air and marginal contact occurs as Grant releases away from the defender.
Grant (POR) gathers the ball with one hand and then takes three steps before releasing the shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) legally contests Grant's (POR) jump shot attempt.
